goals.question: What is the distribution of opening stock prices?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of opening stock prices and identify any potential outliers.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the opening and closing stock prices?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends in the relationship between the opening and closing stock prices.

goals.question: What is the distribution of trading signals?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of each trading signal and identify any potential biases in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of returns on investment?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of returns on investment and identify any potential outliers.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the trading signal and the return on investment?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends in the relationship between the trading signal and the return on investment.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Opening Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Opening Stock Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening stock prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'], c=data['signal'].map({'long': 'green', 'short': 'red', 'neutral': 'blue'}))
    plt.xlabel('Opening Price')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the opening and closing stock prices?', wrap=True)
    
    legend_elements = [plt.Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', label='Long', markerfacecolor='green', markersize=10),
                       plt.Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', label='Short', markerfacecolor='red', markersize=10),
                       plt.Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', label='Neutral', markerfacecolor='blue', markersize=10)]
    plt.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    signal_counts = data['signal'].value_counts()
    signal_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green'])
    plt.title("What is the distribution of trading signals?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Trading Signals")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend(signal_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['ret'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Returns')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Returns on Investment')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of returns on investment?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='ret', by='signal', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the trading signal and the return on investment?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Trading Signal')
    ax.set_ylabel('Return on Investment (%)')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Signal', loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
